<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-514-476  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 514 476.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDN  August 10 1989 v34 n14A p5(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DESC to audit non-JAN parts. (Defense Electronics Supply Center;Joint Army-Navy)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Magnus, Stephen A.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Defense Science Board (DSB) is calling on the DefenseElectronics Supply Center (DESC) to audit non-Joint Army Navy(JAN) parts for military systems, but DESC says it needs a largerbudget to handle the extra work.andP;  The agency wants to encouragethe increased use of cheaper off-the-shelf components whileimproving reliability, and notes that the current practice ofhaving OEMs audit non-JAN parts suppliers individually results incostly, redundant audits.andP;  Non-JAN parts already outnumber JANcomponents in most military systems but have had many problems.andO;The Department of Defense requires commercial semiconductorproducts to meet JAN specifications to gain its highest approval.andO;Other recommendations in the DSB report include expansion of theDESC SMD program, and increasing the use of non-governmentspecifications.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Defense contractsUnited States. Defense Science BoardUnited States. Department of DefenseCost ReductionReportsMilitaryElectronicsOEMsAuditing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>